<TITLE> 72 JS promoted to AS in massive admin shake-up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)  In the single largest move under ongoing administrative shuffles, the government has promoted 72 joint secretaries to additional secretaries, according to separate establishment ministry orders on Tuesday. Some 22 deputy secretary-ranked bureaucrats also saw inter-ministerial transfers. Among the transfers, press officer of the department of land records and survey, Mikail Sipar, and director of the National Library, Mahmudur Rahman, have been appointed to the prime minister's office as directors. Among the 72 promoted to additional secretary, one belongs to the BCS (admin) cadre passing out in 1979, three to the 1981 batch, 45 to the 1982 batch, six to the 1982 special batch and 17 to other years. The 72 transfers are the biggest shake-up in the administration in less than a month since the Awami League-led governmentwhich had accused the previous BNP-led government of politicising the administrationtook office on Jan 6. bdnews24.
